milestones.description: Porterfield and Balbirnie's 201-run partnership is IRE's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 157 between Porterfield and Paul Stirling
Ahmed Raza has broken the record for most ducks (4) in ODIs for UAE, going past Alhashmi's 3
Rohan Mustafa has broken the record for most ODIs (9) as captain for UAE, going past Khurram Khan
Naveed has broken the record for most sixes (12) in ODIs for UAE, going past Shaiman Anwar's 12
Porterfield has scored 24 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for IRE breaking Paul Stirling's record

stories.title: Porterfield, Balbirnie centuries hand UAE second defeat in tri-series
stories.subTitle: UAE v Ireland, tri-series, Dubai
stories.seoTitle: Porterfield, Balbirnie centuries hand UAE second defeat in tri-series
stories.summary: A 201-run second-wicket stand, built around centuries from William Porterfield and Andy Balbirnie, followed by a four-wicket haul from Kevin O'Brien, set up Ireland's 67-run triumph over the hosts
